 eventId: string;\n  roomId: string;\n  startTime: number;\n  endTime: number;\n}\n\nexport interface ScheduleResult {\n  assignments: Assignment[];\n  unscheduled: string[];\n}\n\n/**\n * Detect cycles using Kahn's algorithm and return topological order.\n * Throws if a cycle is detected.\n */\nfunction topologicalSort(events: Event[]): string[] {\n  const eventIds = new Set(events.map(e => e.id));\n  const inDegree = new Map<string, number>();\n  const adjList = new Map<string, string[]>();\n\n  for (const event of events) {\n    inDegree.set(event.id, 0);\n    adjList.set(event.id, []);\n  }\n\n  for (const event of events) {\n    if (!event.prerequisites) continue;\n    for (const prereq of event.prerequisites) {\n      // Self-reference check\n      if (prereq === event.id) {\n        throw new Error(`Cycle detected: event \"${event.id}\" has itself as a prerequisite`);\n      }\n      if (eventIds.has(prereq)) {\n        adjList.get(prereq)!.push(event.id);\n        inDegree.set(event.id, (inDegree.get(event.id) ?? 0) + 1);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  const queue: string[] = [];\n  for (const [id, deg] of inDegree) {\n    if (deg === 0) queue.push(id);\n  }\n\n  const sorted: string[] = [];\n  while (queue.length > 0) {\n    const node = queue.shift()!;\n    sorted.push(node);\n    for (const neighbor of adjList.get(node) ?? []) {\n      const newDeg = (inDegree.get(neighbor) ?? 1) - 1;\n      inDegree.set(neighbor, newDeg);\n      if (newDeg === 0) queue.push(neighbor);\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (sorted.length !== eventIds.size) {\n    throw new Error('Cycle detected in prerequisite graph');\n  }\n\n  return sorted;\n}\n\n/**\n * Find the earliest start time for an event in a specific room,\n * given existing assignments and prerequisite constraints.\n */\nfunction findEarliestStart(\n  event: Event,\n  room: Room,\n  assignments: Assignment[],\n  eventMap: Map<string, Event>,\n  assignmentByEvent: Map<string, Assignment>,\n  options: ScheduleOptions,\n  gap: number,\n): number | null {\n  const attendees = event.attendees ?? 1;\n  if (attendees > room.capacity) return null;\n\n  // Earliest based on prerequisite completion\n  let earliest = options.startTime;\n  if (event.prerequisites) {\n    for (const prereqId of event.prerequisites) {\n      const prereqAssignment = assignmentByEvent.get(prereqId);\n      if (prereqAssignment) {\n        earliest = Math.max(earliest, prereqAssignment.endTime + gap);\n      }\n      // If prereq exists in eventMap but isn't assigned yet, we can't schedule this event\n      if (eventMap.has(prereqId) && !prereqAssignment) {\n        return null;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Get all assignments in this room, sorted by start time\n  const roomAssignments = assignments\n    .filter(a => a.roomId === room.id)\n    .sort((a, b) => a.startTime - b.startTime);\n\n  // Try to fit the event starting from `earliest`\n  // Gap rule: end of one event + gap <= start of next event in same room\n  let candidateStart = earliest;\n\n  for (const existing of roomAssignments) {\n    // Check if we can fit before this existing event (with gap after our event)\n    if (candidateStart + event.duration + gap <= existing.startTime) {\n      break;\n    }\n    // We overlap or are too close; move past this existing event\n    candidateStart = Math.max(candidateStart, existing.endTime + gap);\n  }\n\n  // Check it fits within the time window\n  if (candidateStart + event.duration > options.endTime) return null;\n\n  return candidateStart;\n}\n\n/**\n * Find all valid (room, startTime) placements for an event.\n */\nfunction findAllPlacements(\n  event: Event,\n  rooms: Room[],\n  assignments: Assignment[],\n  eventMap: Map<string, Event>,\n  assignmentByEvent: Map<string, Assignment>,\n  options: ScheduleOptions,\n  gap: number,\n): Array<{ roomId: string; startTime: number }> {\n  const placements: Array<{ roomId: string; startTime: number }> = [];\n\n  // Try preferred room first\n  const sortedRooms = [...rooms];\n  if (event.preferredRoom) {\n    sortedRooms.sort((a, b) => {\n      if (a.id === event.preferredRoom) return -1;\n      if (b.id === event.preferredRoom) return 1;\n      return 0;\n    });\n  }\n\n  for (const room of sortedRooms) {\n    const start = findEarliestStart(event, room, assignments, eventMap, assignmentByEvent, options, gap);\n    if (start !== null) {\n      placements.push({ roomId: room.id, startTime: start });\n    }\n  }\n\n  return placements;\n}\n\n/**\n * Schedule events using backtracking with MCV heuristic.\n */\nexport function schedule(events: Event[], rooms: Room[], options: ScheduleOptions): ScheduleResult {\n  if (events.length === 0) {\n    return { assignments: [], unscheduled: [] };\n  }\n\n  const gap = options.gap ?? 15;\n  const eventMap = new Map<string, Event>(events.map(e => [e.id, e]));\n\n  // Detect cycles — throws on cycle\n  topologicalSort(events);\n\n  // Compute prerequisite depth (longest chain to reach this event)\n  const prereqDepth = new Map<string, number>();\n  function getDepth(eventId: string): number {\n    if (prereqDepth.has(eventId)) return prereqDepth.get(eventId)!;\n    const event = eventMap.get(eventId);\n    if (!event || !event.prerequisites || event.prerequisites.length === 0) {\n      prereqDepth.set(eventId, 0);\n      return 0;\n    }\n    let maxDepth = 0;\n    for (const prereqId of event.prerequisites) {\n      if (eventMap.has(prereqId)) {\n        maxDepth = Math.max(maxDepth, getDepth(prereqId) + 1);\n      }\n    }\n    prereqDepth.set(eventId, maxDepth);\n    return maxDepth;\n  }\n  for (const event of events) {\n    getDepth(event.id);\n  }\n\n  // Count how many valid rooms each event can use (capacity-wise)\n  const validRoomCount = new Map<string, number>();\n  for (const event of events) {\n    const attendees = event.attendees ?? 1;\n    let count = 0;\n    for (const room of rooms) {\n      if (attendees <= room.capacity) count++;\n    }\n    validRoomCount.set(event.id, count);\n  }\n\n  // Collect dependents for each event (events that depend on it)\n  const dependents = new Map<string, Set<string>>();\n  for (const event of events) {\n    dependents.set(event.id, new Set());\n  }\n  for (const event of events) {\n    if (event.prerequisites) {\n      for (const prereqId of event.prerequisites) {\n        if (dependents.has(prereqId)) {\n          dependents.get(prereqId)!.add(event.id);\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Count all transitive dependents\n  const transitiveDependentCount = new Map<string, number>();\n  function countDependents(eventId: string, visited: Set<string>): number {\n    if (transitiveDependentCount.has(eventId)) return transitiveDependentCount.get(eventId)!;\n    let count = 0;\n    for (const dep of dependents.get(eventId) ?? []) {\n      if (!visited.has(dep)) {\n        visited.add(dep);\n        count += 1 + countDependents(dep, visited);\n      }\n    }\n    transitiveDependentCount.set(eventId, count);\n    return count;\n  }\n  for (const event of events) {\n    countDependents(event.id, new Set([event.id]));\n  }\n\n  // Use a greedy approach with smart ordering, then try to improve\n  function greedySchedule(eventOrder: Event[]): { assignments: Assignment[]; unscheduled: string[] } {\n    const assignments: Assignment[] = [];\n    const assignmentByEvent = new Map<string, Assignment>();\n    const unscheduled: string[] = [];\n\n    for (const event of eventOrder) {\n      const placements = findAllPlacements(event, rooms, assignments, eventMap, assignmentByEvent, options, gap);\n\n      if (placements.length === 0) {\n        unscheduled.push(event.id);\n        continue;\n      }\n\n      // Pick the best placement:\n      // 1. Prefer the preferred room\n      // 2. Among equal preferences, pick the earliest start time\n      // 3. Among equal start times, pick the smallest room (leave large rooms for large events)\n      let best = placements[0];\n      for (let i = 1; i < placements.length; i++) {\n        const p = placements[i];\n        const bestIsPreferred = best.roomId === event.preferredRoom;\n        const pIsPreferred = p.roomId === event.preferredRoom;\n\n        if (pIsPreferred && !bestIsPreferred) {\n          best = p;\n        } else if (pIsPreferred === bestIsPreferred) {\n          if (p.startTime < best.startTime) {\n            best = p;\n          } else if (p.startTime === best.startTime) {\n            const bestRoom = rooms.find(r => r.id === best.roomId)!;\n            const pRoom = rooms.find(r => r.id === p.roomId)!;\n            if (pRoom.capacity < bestRoom.capacity) {\n              best = p;\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      }\n\n      const assignment: Assignment = {\n        eventId: event.id,\n        roomId: best.roomId,\n        startTime: best.startTime,\n        endTime: best.startTime + event.duration,\n      };\n      assignments.push(assignment);\n      assignmentByEvent.set(event.id, assignment);\n    }\n\n    return { assignments, unscheduled };\n  }\n\n  // Try multiple orderings and pick the one that schedules the most events\n  function createOrderings(): Event[][] {\n    const orderings: Event[][] = [];\n\n    // Ordering 1: prerequisite depth first, then fewer valid rooms, then more dependents\n    const order1 = [...events].sort((a, b) => {\n      const depthA = prereqDepth.get(a.id) ?? 0;\n      const depthB = prereqDepth.get(b.id) ?? 0;\n      if (depthA !== depthB) return depthA - depthB;\n      const roomsA = validRoomCount.get(a.id) ?? 0;\n      const roomsB = validRoomCount.get(b.id) ?? 0;\n      if (roomsA !== roomsB) return roomsA - roomsB;\n      const depsA = transitiveDependentCount.get(a.id) ?? 0;\n      const depsB = transitiveDependentCount.get(b.id) ?? 0;\n      return depsB - depsA;\n    });\n    orderings.push(order1);\n\n    // Ordering 2: MCV — fewest valid rooms first, then prerequisite depth\n    const order2 = [...events].sort((a, b) => {\n      const roomsA = validRoomCount.get(a.id) ?? 0;\n      const roomsB = validRoomCount.get(b.id) ?? 0;\n      if (roomsA !== roomsB) return roomsA - roomsB;\n      const depthA = prereqDepth.get(a.id) ?? 0;\n      const depthB = prereqDepth.get(b.id) ?? 0;\n      if (depthA !== depthB) return depthA - depthB;\n      return (b.duration) - (a.duration);\n    });\n    orderings.push(order2);\n\n    // Ordering 3: Most dependents first (events that unlock others)\n    const order3 = [...events].sort((a, b) => {\n      const depsA = transitiveDependentCount.get(a.id) ?? 0;\n      const depsB = transitiveDependentCount.get(b.id) ?? 0;\n      if (depsA !== depsB) return depsB - depsA;\n      const depthA = prereqDepth.get(a.id) ?? 0;\n      const depthB = prereqDepth.get(b.id) ?? 0;\n      return depthA - depthB;\n    });\n    orderings.push(order3);\n\n    // Ordering 4: Shortest duration first (pack more events)\n    const order4 = [...events].sort((a, b) => {\n      const depthA = prereqDepth.get(a.id) ?? 0;\n      const depthB = prereqDepth.get(b.id) ?? 0;\n      if (depthA !== depthB) return depthA - depthB;\n      return a.duration - b.duration;\n    });\n    orderings.push(order4);\n\n    // Ordering 5: Longest duration first (place hard-to-fit events first)\n    const order5 = [...events].sort((a, b) => {\n      const depthA = prereqDepth.get(a.id) ?? 0;\n      const depthB = prereqDepth.get(b.id) ?? 0;\n      if (depthA !== depthB) return depthA - depthB;\n      return b.duration - a.duration;\n    });\n    orderings.push(order5);\n\n    // Ordering 6: Largest attendees first (hardest capacity constraint first)\n    const order6 = [...events].sort((a, b) => {\n      const depthA = prereqDepth.get(a.id) ?? 0;\n      const depthB = prereqDepth.get(b.id) ?? 0;\n      if (depthA !== depthB) return depthA - depthB;\n      return (b.attendees ?? 1) - (a.attendees ?? 1);\n    });\n    orderings.push(order6);\n\n    return orderings;\n  }\n\n  // Ensure orderings respect prerequisite constraints\n  functio